{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I was speaking to a group of about 300 kids,"},{"time":3000,"text":"ages six to eight, at a children's museum,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and I brought with me a bag full of legs,"},{"time":9000,"text":"similar to the kinds of things you see up here,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and had them laid out on a table for the kids."},{"time":13000,"text":"And, from my experience, you know, kids are naturally curious"},{"time":17000,"text":"about what they don't know, or don't understand,"},{"time":19000,"text":"or is foreign to them."},{"time":21000,"text":"They only learn to be frightened of those differences"},{"time":23000,"text":"when an adult influences them to behave that way,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and maybe censors that natural curiosity,"},{"time":29000,"text":"or you know, reins in the question-asking"},{"time":32000,"text":"in the hopes of them being polite little kids."},{"time":34000,"text":"So I just pictured a first grade teacher out in the lobby"},{"time":38000,"text":"with these unruly kids, saying, \"Now, whatever you do,"},{"time":41000,"text":"don't stare at her legs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"But, of course, that's the point."},{"time":45000,"text":"That's why I was there, I wanted to invite them to look and explore."},{"time":48000,"text":"So I made a deal with the adults"},{"time":52000,"text":"that the kids could come in without any adults for two minutes"},{"time":55000,"text":"on their own."},{"time":57000,"text":"The doors open, the kids descend on this table of legs,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and they are poking and prodding, and they're wiggling toes,"},{"time":64000,"text":"and they're trying to put their full weight on the sprinting leg"},{"time":66000,"text":"to see what happens with that."},{"time":68000,"text":"And I said, \"Kids, really quickly --"},{"time":70000,"text":"I woke up this morning, I decided I wanted to be able to jump over a house --"},{"time":74000,"text":"nothing too big, two or three stories --"},{"time":76000,"text":"but, if you could think of any animal, any superhero, any cartoon character,"},{"time":81000,"text":"anything you can dream up right now,"},{"time":83000,"text":"what kind of legs would you build me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"And immediately a voice shouted, \"Kangaroo!\""},{"time":88000,"text":"\"No, no, no! Should be a frog!\""},{"time":90000,"text":"\"No. It should be Go Go Gadget!\""},{"time":92000,"text":"\"No, no, no! It should be the Incredibles.\""},{"time":94000,"text":"And other things that I don't -- aren't familiar with."},{"time":97000,"text":"And then, one eight-year-old said,"},{"time":99000,"text":"\"Hey, why wouldn't you want to fly too?\""},{"time":104000,"text":"And the whole room, including me, was like, \"Yeah.\""},{"time":107000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":109000,"text":"And just like that, I went from being a woman"},{"time":112000,"text":"that these kids would have been trained to see as \"disabled\""},{"time":116000,"text":"to somebody that had potential that their bodies didn't have yet."},{"time":121000,"text":"Somebody that might even be super-abled."},{"time":123000,"text":"Interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"So some of you actually saw me at TED, 11 years ago."},{"time":130000,"text":"And there's been a lot of talk about how life-changing this conference is"},{"time":134000,"text":"for both speakers and attendees, and I am no exception."},{"time":138000,"text":"TED literally was the launch pad to the next decade of my life's exploration."},{"time":144000,"text":"At the time, the legs I presented were groundbreaking in prosthetics."},{"time":149000,"text":"I had woven carbon fiber sprinting legs"},{"time":151000,"text":"modeled after the hind leg of a cheetah,"},{"time":153000,"text":"which you may have seen on stage yesterday."},{"time":155000,"text":"And also these very life-like, intrinsically painted silicone legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"So at the time, it was my opportunity to put a call out"},{"time":165000,"text":"to innovators outside the traditional medical prosthetic community"},{"time":169000,"text":"to come bring their talent to the science and to the art"},{"time":173000,"text":"of building legs."},{"time":175000,"text":"So that we can stop compartmentalizing form, function and aesthetic,"},{"time":180000,"text":"and assigning them different values."},{"time":182000,"text":"Well, lucky for me, a lot of people answered that call."},{"time":186000,"text":"And the journey started, funny enough, with a TED conference attendee --"},{"time":191000,"text":"Chee Pearlman, who hopefully is in the audience somewhere today."},{"time":194000,"text":"She was the editor then of a magazine called ID,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and she gave me a cover story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"This started an incredible journey."},{"time":203000,"text":"Curious encounters were happening to me at the time;"},{"time":205000,"text":"I'd been accepting numerous invitations to speak"},{"time":208000,"text":"on the design of the cheetah legs around the world."},{"time":211000,"text":"And people would come up to me after the conference, after my talk,"},{"time":214000,"text":"men and women."},{"time":216000,"text":"And the conversation would go something like this,"},{"time":218000,"text":"\"You know Aimee, you're very attractive."},{"time":222000,"text":"You don't look disabled.\""},{"time":224000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":225000,"text":"I thought, \"Well, that's amazing,"},{"time":227000,"text":"because I don't feel disabled.\""},{"time":229000,"text":"And it really opened my eyes to this conversation"},{"time":234000,"text":"that could be explored, about beauty."},{"time":236000,"text":"What does a beautiful woman have to look like?"},{"time":239000,"text":"What is a sexy body?"},{"time":241000,"text":"And interestingly, from an identity standpoint,"},{"time":243000,"text":"what does it mean to have a disability?"},{"time":246000,"text":"I mean, people -- Pamela Anderson has more prosthetic in her body than I do."},{"time":249000,"text":"Nobody calls her disabled."},{"time":251000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"So this magazine, through the hands of graphic designer Peter Saville,"},{"time":261000,"text":"went to fashion designer Alexander McQueen, and photographer Nick Knight,"},{"time":266000,"text":"who were also interested in exploring that conversation."},{"time":268000,"text":"So, three months after TED I found myself on a plane"},{"time":271000,"text":"to London, doing my first fashion shoot,"},{"time":276000,"text":"which resulted in this cover --"},{"time":277000,"text":"\"Fashion-able\"?"},{"time":280000,"text":"Three months after that, I did my first runway show for Alexander McQueen"},{"time":284000,"text":"on a pair of hand-carved wooden legs made from solid ash."},{"time":289000,"text":"Nobody knew -- everyone thought they were wooden boots."},{"time":292000,"text":"Actually, I have them on stage with me:"},{"time":295000,"text":"grapevines, magnolias -- truly stunning."},{"time":300000,"text":"Poetry matters."},{"time":303000,"text":"Poetry is what elevates the banal and neglected object"},{"time":308000,"text":"to a realm of art."},{"time":310000,"text":"It can transform the thing that might have made people fearful"},{"time":316000,"text":"into something that invites them to look,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and look a little longer,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and maybe even understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"I learned this firsthand with my next adventure."},{"time":327000,"text":"The artist Matthew Barney, in his film opus called the \"The Cremaster Cycle.\""},{"time":331000,"text":"This is where it really hit home for me --"},{"time":334000,"text":"that my legs could be wearable sculpture."},{"time":336000,"text":"And even at this point, I started to move away from the need to replicate human-ness"},{"time":343000,"text":"as the only aesthetic ideal."},{"time":345000,"text":"So we made what people lovingly referred to as glass legs"},{"time":349000,"text":"even though they're actually optically clear polyurethane,"},{"time":353000,"text":"a.k.a. bowling ball material."},{"time":355000,"text":"Heavy!"},{"time":356000,"text":"Then we made these legs that are cast in soil"},{"time":358000,"text":"with a potato root system growing in them, and beetroots out the top,"},{"time":362000,"text":"and a very lovely brass toe."},{"time":364000,"text":"That's a good close-up of that one."},{"time":366000,"text":"Then another character was a half-woman, half-cheetah --"},{"time":368000,"text":"a little homage to my life as an athlete."},{"time":370000,"text":"14 hours of prosthetic make-up"},{"time":373000,"text":"to get into a creature that had articulated paws,"},{"time":377000,"text":"claws and a tail that whipped around,"},{"time":381000,"text":"like a gecko."},{"time":383000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":385000,"text":"And then another pair of legs we collaborated on were these --"},{"time":389000,"text":"look like jellyfish legs,"},{"time":391000,"text":"also polyurethane."},{"time":393000,"text":"And the only purpose that these legs can serve,"},{"time":396000,"text":"outside the context of the film,"},{"time":399000,"text":"is to provoke the senses and ignite the imagination."},{"time":402000,"text":"So whimsy matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"Today, I have over a dozen pair of prosthetic legs"},{"time":411000,"text":"that various people have made for me,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and with them I have different negotiations of the terrain under my feet,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and I can change my height --"},{"time":419000,"text":"I have a variable of five different heights."},{"time":421000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":423000,"text":"Today, I'm 6'1\"."},{"time":425000,"text":"And I had these legs made a little over a year ago"},{"time":428000,"text":"at Dorset Orthopedic in England"},{"time":430000,"text":"and when I brought them home to Manhattan,"},{"time":432000,"text":"my first night out on the town, I went to a very fancy party."},{"time":434000,"text":"And a girl was there who has known me for years"},{"time":437000,"text":"at my normal 5'8\"."},{"time":439000,"text":"Her mouth dropped open when she saw me,"},{"time":441000,"text":"and she went, \"But you're so tall!\""},{"time":444000,"text":"And I said, \"I know. Isn't it fun?\""},{"time":446000,"text":"I mean, it's a little bit like wearing stilts on stilts,"},{"time":448000,"text":"but I have an entirely new relationship to door jams"},{"time":451000,"text":"that I never expected I would ever have."},{"time":453000,"text":"And I was having fun with it."},{"time":456000,"text":"And she looked at me,"},{"time":458000,"text":"and she said, \"But, Aimee, that's not fair.\""},{"time":460000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":463000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":465000,"text":"And the incredible thing was she really meant it."},{"time":469000,"text":"It's not fair that you can change your height,"},{"time":471000,"text":"as you want it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"And that's when I knew --"},{"time":475000,"text":"that's when I knew that the conversation with society"},{"time":478000,"text":"has changed profoundly"},{"time":480000,"text":"in this last decade."},{"time":482000,"text":"It is no longer a conversation about overcoming deficiency."},{"time":487000,"text":"It's a conversation about augmentation."},{"time":489000,"text":"It's a conversation about potential."},{"time":493000,"text":"A prosthetic limb doesn't represent the need to replace loss anymore."},{"time":498000,"text":"It can stand as a symbol that the wearer"},{"time":501000,"text":"has the power to create whatever it is that they want to create"},{"time":504000,"text":"in that space."},{"time":506000,"text":"So people that society once considered to be disabled"},{"time":509000,"text":"can now become the architects of their own identities"},{"time":514000,"text":"and indeed continue to change those identities"},{"time":516000,"text":"by designing their bodies"},{"time":518000,"text":"from a place of empowerment."},{"time":521000,"text":"And what is exciting to me so much right now"},{"time":526000,"text":"is that by combining cutting-edge technology --"},{"time":530000,"text":"robotics, bionics --"},{"time":532000,"text":"with the age-old poetry,"},{"time":534000,"text":"we are moving closer to understanding our collective humanity."},{"time":540000,"text":"I think that if we want to discover the full potential"},{"time":545000,"text":"in our humanity,"},{"time":547000,"text":"we need to celebrate those heartbreaking strengths"},{"time":551000,"text":"and those glorious disabilities that we all have."},{"time":554000,"text":"I think of Shakespeare's Shylock:"},{"time":557000,"text":"\"If you prick us, do we not bleed,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and if you tickle us, do we not laugh?\""},{"time":564000,"text":"It is our humanity,"},{"time":567000,"text":"and all the potential within it,"},{"time":569000,"text":"that makes us beautiful."},{"time":572000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":573000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}